Patch Set 7: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

This looks good. However, its actually subject to a race condition that will preserve the original bug. If events happen in the following sequence, the original bug will persist.

1. On client1, upload fails and api gets image metadata from registry
2. Client 2 calls api and says delete, api deletes image from registry
3. Back with client1's request, the api thinks the image is in 'saving' due to step 1, and so updates the metadata to 'killed' and saves it in the registry.

The solution, again, is to push the verification to the database which I suppose is the only place in our service that can truly be atomic.

Normally I would think "+2 this fixes 99.9% of the problem" but I'm afraid it also makes that 0.1% about 500 times harder to debug so I just wanna push back a little bit. I think maybe this patch should be refactored to use what you have in https://review.openstack.org/#/c/52409/9  to eliminate this race condition.

1. On client1, upload fails and api gets image metadata from registry

2. Client 2 calls api and says delete, api deletes image from registry

3. Back with client1's request, the api thinks the image is in 'saving' due to step 1, and so updates the metadata to 'killed' and saves it in the registry.
